29/10/2003
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- A military parade and air show were held in Thessaloniki on Tuesday (28 October) to mark a national holiday commemorating Greece's refusal to bow to fascist Italy in 1940 and Thessaloniki's liberation from the Ottomans in 1912.
In his message to the nation, Prime Minister Costas Simitis said Greece is powerful enough to take on new historical challenges, such as prosperity and security in Europe.
For his part, Defence Minister Yiannos Papantoniou vowed to continue modernising the armed forces.
(ANA - 28/10/03)
